<br>
For 30aa points you can train scf all the way up (up to level 3 of magic fury mastery). Let's assume that that makes you crit 10% of the time (which would be insane, since you'd only get a total of 3% critting for 18aa points, you obviously get more)<br>
<br>
With FoT every 10th cast lands for 2k extra damage, so if you cast 50 spells in 30 minutes (less than 2 a min, done easily) you outdamage host. With black steel you don't need many more casts.<br>
<br>
And fury doesn't lose to enraging mobs, doesn't lose effectiveness when you're hit and doesn't fail due to aes.<br>
<br>
Wouldn't it make sense from a balance perspective for the mage pets to = the shaman = the wizzie pets? And then the more pet centered you are the more pets your Call brings?<br>
<br>
So long story short: For this to be an ability you would want to spend points on, verant has to begin by making it a minute long, make it so mini-pets can't be agroed or take ae damage, and then tune the pets up so that there is a reason for spending points in this rather than fury. I'll tell you right now that won't happen, so save your aa points on this one, or at the very least get only level 1, as this ability scales downward with points spent. (5400dam for 5aa points is respectable, better than scf2 for 6points)<br>
<br>
